Five years ago Kristen Ritter came bursting onto the MCU scene breathing life to the lesser-known Jessica Jones. While the series has had some highs and lows, Season 1 of Jessica Jones stands out for tackling tough subject matter, handling adult themes, and portraying PTSD in a way no superhero show had before. Add an enigmatic performance by David Tennant as the sadistic Kilgrave to the mix and you have a "Jewel" of Superhero television. Join us as we revisit the first time we met Jessica Jones on Netflix and review Jessica Jones Season 1!

